# TypeScript Strict Checks

Apply these checks on TypeScript edits.

- Keep `strict`-safe typings: no `any`; use `unknown` + narrowing.
- Add explicit return types for exported functions.
- Use named exports only; do not introduce default exports.
- Keep modules side-effect free and tree-shakeable.
- Prefer one focused function per file and keep files small.
- Use type-only imports/exports where applicable.

Before finishing substantial TS changes:

- Run `npm run format`.
- Run `npm run lint`.
- Run `npm run test` when logic behavior changes.
- Ensure `npm run build` succeeds for declaration/type integrity.
